{"id":"smoke-zg6b","title":"Fix FS_WRITEFILE path boundary check: bypassable with prefix string matching","description":"SECURITY: The FS_WRITEFILE handler uses startsWith(homedir) to validate write paths, which is not boundary-safe. Example: home=/home/alice, path=/home/alice-malicious/file.txt passes the check despite being outside the home directory. Symlinks can also escape the boundary.

Fix: resolve both paths with realpath, then use path.relative(home, target) and reject if the relative path starts with '..' or is absolute. Use segment-aware boundary checks, not raw string prefix. Consider an explicit allowlist of writable roots.

Add regression tests for: path traversal (/home/user-other), symlink escape, and '..' injection.","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","owner":"chanjun.park@wisetechglobal.com","created_at":"2026-03-16T04:02:38Z","created_by":"marlboro-red","updated_at":"2026-03-16T04:02:38Z"}

{"id":"smoke-rvc9","title":"No error boundaries around core renderer components","description":"Only plugin components have error boundaries (PluginErrorBoundary.tsx). Core UI subtrees — Canvas, Sidebar, ConfigPanel, TerminalWindow, FileViewerWindow — have none. Any render error in these components crashes the entire app.

Impact: A single terminal or file viewer crash takes down the full UI. Users lose all work.

Fix: Add React Error Boundaries around Canvas, Sidebar, and other major component subtrees with graceful fallback UI (e.g. 'This component crashed, click to retry').","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"chanjun.park@wisetechglobal.com","created_at":"2026-03-16T05:08:09Z","created_by":"marlboro-red","updated_at":"2026-03-16T05:08:09Z"}

{"id":"smoke-fir5","title":"PTY data IPC has no batching or backpressure","description":"ipcHandlers.ts:226-231: Every node-pty data event immediately calls win.webContents.send(PTY_DATA_FROM_PTY). High-output processes (find /, cat large-file, build logs) send thousands of IPC messages per second, starving the main process event loop and flooding the renderer.

Impact: UI freezes during heavy terminal output. Main process becomes unresponsive.

Fix: Implement IPC message batching — accumulate PTY data chunks over a short window (e.g. 4-8ms) and send as a single batched message. Add backpressure mechanism to pause PTY reads when renderer can't keep up.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","owner":"chanjun.park@wisetechglobal.com","created_at":"2026-03-16T05:08:26Z","created_by":"marlboro-red","updated_at":"2026-03-16T05:08:26Z"}

{"id":"smoke-57c8","title":"Viewport culling O(n) scan needs optimization for large canvases","description":"useViewportCulling.ts:45-66: Every pan/zoom change triggers an O(n) sequential scan of all sessions with no spatial indexing. With 100+ sessions, this fires 10+ times/sec during panning, causing frame drops.

Also: ConnectorLayer.tsx:93-140 re-renders entire SVG on any session position change. Canvas.tsx:157-266 renderSessionElement lacks per-session memoization — all windows re-render when any session changes.

Fix: Consider spatial indexing (quadtree) for viewport culling at scale. Add debounce to pan/zoom-triggered recalculations. Memoize individual window components with React.memo().","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","owner":"chanjun.park@wisetechglobal.com","created_at":"2026-03-16T05:09:14Z","created_by":"marlboro-red","updated_at":"2026-03-16T05:09:14Z"}

